<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870522-0144 </DOCNO><HL> Topps Makes Stock Offer,Selling 1.7 Million Shares</HL><DD> 05/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TOPPSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Topps Co., the chewing gum and baseball card concern, launched an initial offering on a somewhat smaller scale than planned.    The company sold 1.7 million shares at $13 each in an offering headed by Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co. The shares closed at $12.875 a share on first-day volume of 1.3 million shares, after trading as high as $13.25.    The company had proposed an offering of as many as 4.5 million shares at a price estimated at $15 to $18 a share. Of the actual offering, 1,325,000 shares were sold by selling shareholders and 375,000 shares by the company.    The company went private in 1984 in a leveraged buyout valued at about $96 million. At the offering price, the company's 14.5 million shares would be valued at about $187 million. </TEXT></DOC>